reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Sweet Blend of Style and Functionality
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the MOFII Wireless Keyboard and Mouse in the delightful Milk Tea color with round keycaps, and I couldn't be happier with my choice. This keyboard and mouse set combines style, comfort, and functionality to create an exceptional user experience.The standout feature of this set is undoubtedly its charming Milk Tea color scheme. The soft and warm tones bring a touch of elegance and uniqueness to my workspace. It's a refreshing departure from the traditional black or white peripherals, adding a tasteful pop of personality to my desk. The round keycaps further enhance the visual appeal, giving the keyboard a retro and playful vibe.Beyond its aesthetics, this wireless keyboard and mouse set delivers impressive functionality. The keyboard connects seamlessly to my device via wireless technology, providing a clutter-free workspace. The keys are well-spaced and responsive, allowing for comfortable and accurate typing. Whether I'm working on documents, writing emails, or simply browsing the web, the keyboard's tactile feedback and smooth keystrokes make the typing experience enjoyable.The inclusion of a wireless mouse adds convenience and versatility to the set. The mouse tracks smoothly on various surfaces, and the ergonomic design fits comfortably in my hand, reducing strain during long hours of use. It offers responsive and precise cursor movement, allowing for seamless navigation and control. The wireless connection is reliable, eliminating the need for tangled cables and providing flexibility in positioning.Setting up the MOFII Wireless Keyboard and Mouse is a breeze. The plug-and-play functionality ensures a hassle-free installation process. The keyboard and mouse quickly pair with my device, and I can start using them within seconds. The wireless range is impressive, giving me the freedom to move around my workspace without losing connectivity.Another notable feature is the long battery life of both the keyboard and mouse. With energy-saving technology, they can operate for extended periods before requiring a battery change. This durability and efficiency save me the hassle of constantly replacing batteries, allowing me to focus on my work without interruptions.Overall, the MOFII Wireless Keyboard and Mouse in the Milk Tea color with round keycaps is a delightful combination of style and functionality. Its eye-catching design, comfortable typing experience, and wireless convenience make it an excellent choice for anyone seeking a reliable and aesthetically pleasing peripheral set. Whether for work or leisure, this set elevates the overall user experience and adds a touch of charm to any desk.Disclaimer: I purchased this product for personal use and received no incentive or compensation for this review. My review is based solely on my own experience and satisfaction with the product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Worked great for the first 14 months
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love this keyboard and mouse set. It worked really well with absolutely no issues for over a year. I moved offices and with my new setup, the mouse is really lagging. I read other reviews that mention this, but I never had the issue at all until moving offices. I do really think it is due to the proximity of the mouse to the usb that goes into your laptop or tower. I want to believe this is the problem, but sometimes I have it right next to the connection and it still lags. The lag is so bad that it makes it almost unusable. I would normally just think that based on the price the unit is just ready to be replaced and happily buy a new one. However, based on the other reviews, I worry a new one might have the same issue and I was lucky to get a mouse that worked for over a year with my first purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Not suitable for gaming and extortionate to return
reviews.reviewText: I was so disappointed by this keyboard.After reading so many positive reviews I was excited to get the keyboard, and spending £70+ I figured it would be suitable for some basic gameplay as well as typing. It wasn't, the keys stick down and cause you to get stuck moving in one direction.I tried to get a refund but the seller sent me a non paid for returns label which cost almost 1/2 the price of the keyboard to return. Can't recommend this or risking any other keyboard purchases from unknown/lesser brands.
